  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Rural Women's Economic Empowerment (RWEE) joint programme preparatory phase - finalise programme operational modality/geographical programme location with Government (Salary of the WEE consultant)\r\n\r\nDevelop a framework for the Gender Equality and Social Inclusion (GESI) strategy of the Agriculture Development Strategy (ADS) (RWEE joint programme)\r\n\r\nProvide techanical support MoAD to institutionalise monitoring gender responsiveness in the ADS implementation (RWEE joint programme)\r\n\r\n RWEE joint programme preparatory phase - Conduct situation analysis and carry out the baseline assessment \r\n\r\nProvide technical and financial support the National Planning Commission to establish a working group of feminist economists to provide technical advice and policy  guidance on women's economic empowerment\r\n\r\nSupport the finalisation of  the National Plan of Action on Foreign Employment and Reintegration Programme Guideline \r\n\r\nEstablish a research advisory committee at UN Women in consultation with the NPC and the working group of feminist economists to provide advisory support to ensure that knowledge products are of the highest standard both in terms of research content as well as an effective tool for policy advocacy"
    },
    "ne": null
